instruction: Can you give an example of a complex project you've worked on that involved multiple teams and stakeholders? How did you collaborate with them to ensure its success?
output:
Scenario: You are the project manager for a team that is working on a large, complex project. The team has a number of stakeholders, including the product owner, the project manager, the architect, and others. There are multiple team members who are working on the project, and each of these teams needs to collaborate and communicate with one another.


These teams need to work together to develop a solution that will meet the requirements of all of the stakeholders, as well as meet the needs of the project manager. They need to work together to complete the project on time and within budget.


Solution: The project team collaborates to develop a plan that ensures all of the stakeholders are satisfied with the final product. The project team also communicates with the stakeholders to ensure that the plan meets their needs and is consistent with their preferences.

Also, the project team ensures the plan meets the requirements of the project manager, the product owner, and the architect. The team collaborates to develop the plan, and they also communicate with the stakeholders to ensure the plan is consistent with their preferences.


At the end of the project, the team is pleased with the outcome. They feel that the plan and the communication with the stakeholders helped them meet their goals.

output: Relaxation is the most effective way to handle stress, and it can be done many ways. therapeutic meditation is a great way to relax, and it can be done alone or with a friend. aerobic exercise, such as walking, swimming, or yoga, is also a great way to relax. Finally, listening to relaxing music or watching a relaxing movie can also help you relax.

instruction: What are the differences between plant-based and animal-based protein sources?
output: A plant-based source of protein is made from plants, which are the primary source of protein for people. Many people are also able to eat fish or seafood as a source of protein. People may choose to eat beans, lentils, nuts, seeds, and other plant-based protein sources instead of meat or dairy products. People may also choose to eat eggs or dairy products as a source of protein.

instruction: Hi, I'd like to learn how to play racquetball. Can you explain the game to me?
output:
Hi there! You've come to the right place at the right time! racquetball is a very easy game to learn. It's a great exercise that targets all the major muscle groups, and you'll feel a lot of improvement in a few months. racquetball is a great way to build coordination, muscle strength, and balance, and you'll find that you'll be able to play much harder and longer too!

The object of racquetball is to hit the ball back and forth across the court as fast as possible. You hit the ball with both feet, and the goal is to hit it with both hands. You should aim to hit the ball with both hands and both feet at the same time, which will help you gain control over the ball and make it fly further and harder.


You can learn how to play racquetball by playing with a racquet and some balls, or by playing a racquetball-specific game. You can also watch some racquetball instructional videos to get an idea of how the game is played. You'll also need racquetball shoes, a racquet, and some balls to play racquetball.

Racquetball is a great exercise to help you build coordination and strength, and you'll find that you'll enjoy the game a whole lot more after you get started.

instruction: why the sky is blue?
output: Although blue is a naturally occurring color, scientists are not sure why it looks blue. Some speculate that blue light from the sun causes water in the Earth's oceans to absorb the light, resulting in the blue color. Other explanations for blue skies include variations in Earth's atmosphere and clouds, as well as changes in Earth's orbit around the sun. Scientists also look for correlations between the color of the sky and changes in climate, such as the changes in temperature and rainfall that occur when the seasons change in spring and fall.

instruction: What if people only valued and took pride in the things that were true about themselves?
output:
******************

Briefly describe the topic of your essay.

As people, we all have certain core values that guide our behavior. We believe in certain things, and we try to live our lives in accordance with these values. The values we hold most dear are honesty, loyalty, respect, empathy, and self-respect. We want to be respected for who we are, and we want to live our lives in ways that honor these core values. People who are dishonest, selfish, and disrespectful violate these values, and they are also untrue to themselves. They lack integrity, and they are not living up to their own values.


******************

What are some of the costs and benefits of valuing the truth?

Dishonesty can have negative consequences for our lives. People who are dishonest often feel they have nothing to lose, and they are unwilling to take responsibility for their actions. They often feel they have no control over their lives, and they feel they are powerless to change their behavior. They also find it difficult to accept responsibility for their actions, and they often feel they have to keep others at bay. Honesty can also have positive consequences, as it can help people recognize their own mistakes and learn from them. output:
## Organizing an Event

It's easy to get caught up in the details of an event, but the most important thing is to make sure everything is running smoothly. Make sure you have the right equipment, the right people, the right programs, and the right message. An event is a great way to share your knowledge and to get the word out about your organization.


### Planning an Event

The best way to plan an event is to divide it into several smaller steps. Start by identifying the key topics that you want to cover and then brainstorm a few ideas for each topic. Then you can divide the planning into the following three steps:

1. Identify the attendees
2. Organize the program
3. Promote the event

Once you've identified the attendees, you'll need to choose a program that will appeal to the audience you want to reach. You can create a program that's both informative and entertaining, or you can create a program that's more focused on the message you want to share. Once you've chosen the program, you'll need to decide on a promotion strategy to get the word out about your event. You can do this by developing a promotional schedule that includes a variety of media, such as direct mail pieces, fliers, and social media posts. You can also develop a website that will help you market your event and spread the word about your organization.


### Promoting an Event

Once you've organized your program, it's time to start promoting your event. You can do this by developing a variety of marketing strategies, such as advertising in local and regional publications, distributing fliers at events, and participating in community activities.

DIY Water Chiller
Required items are: Ice-maker, Icebox/cooler, Temperature regulator, Aquarium pump x2, 12V power supply
output:
Build a Water Chiller

The goal of a water chiller is to reduce the amount of water needed to produce a given amount of electricity. The chiller should be able to reduce the amount of water by 10% to 15% while still providing the same amount of electricity. This is commonly done by using a reverse osmosis water filter to remove impurities from the water. The chiller should also have a temperature regulator to keep the water within a safe temperature range. The chiller should also include an Aquarium pump to circulate the water through the chiller. The chiller should also include 12V power supply to keep the chiller running.

instruction: Explain sarcoidosis to me like I’m a five year old
output:
Sarcoidosis is a chronic inflammatory disease that affects the skin and the lungs. It is most commonly caused by exposure to environmental particles, such as dust or smoke, and it is also thought to be caused by a genetically inherited susceptibility. Symptoms may include shortness of breath, a persistent cough, weight loss, and a characteristic skin rash that may appear soon after exposure.

Sarcoidosis is usually diagnosed through a lung biopsy, during which a sample of the patient's lung tissue is removed for examination under a microscope.

There are several treatment options available, including medications to help control the symptoms, and lifestyle changes that can help control the inflammation.

Symptoms usually improve with treatment, and diagnosis and treatment usually occur together.

For more information, see your doctor or call your doctor for advice about sarcoidosis.

instruction: “One One was a race horse Two Two was one too. One One won one race. Two Two won one too.” How many horses are in this story?
output:
C

The story of One One and Two Two is a folktale about two racehorses who won one race apiece. The two horses are described as one of the best horses in the country and the other as the second best. The two horses are described as being friends, and the story ends with the horses being asked to walk on the same day. The horses are said to have been friends for many years, and One One and Two Two lived together happily until One One died of old age. The story has been told many times throughout history, and is a good example of a folktale.

Certain health conditions may cause the body to produce too much stomach acid. If stomach acid isn't kept under control, it can cause a condition known as ulcer, in which the stomach lining becomes inflamed. instruction:
What is the difference betwean interpreted compiled and JIT-ed programming language, can you also tell me some benefits of each type of language?
Can you give me at least 3 examples from each of these categories of programming languages?
output:
ogl.net

JIT-ed languages are compiled languages that are optimized for execution on a particular hardware platform. JIT-ed languages are generally more efficient than interpreted languages because the compiler can re-use the code already in memory to speed up execution. Interpreted languages, on the other hand, must load the entire program into memory at startup, which can take longer to execute. JIT-ed languages tend to be more efficient on general-purpose CPUs such as the Intel x86, AMD64, and PowerPC processors.

instruction: I'm trying to learn how to install window blinds.
output:
Scenario:

You need to install window blinds in your home. Installing window blinds is fairly simple. You'll need to determine the size of your window and select the window blinds that will best fit your window. You'll also want to select the style of window blinds that will best match your windows. Finally, you'll need to install the window blinds to your window frame and seal them in place with silicone caulk. 
You can learn more about window blinds by reading our how-to page. 


[!] To install window blinds, you'll first need to determine the size of your window. You'll want to measure the inside of your window, making sure you have enough room to install the window blinds. You'll also want to select the window blinds that will best fit your window. You'll also want to select the style of window blinds that will best match your windows. Finally, you'll want to install the window blinds to your window frame and seal them in place with silicone caulk. 
You can learn more about window blinds by reading our how-to page. 


[!] To clean your window blinds, you'll first need to remove the blinds from your window. You'll want to remove the blinds from the inside of your window, making sure to remove all the blinds and gaps in the blinds. You'll also want to wipe down the inside of your window to remove any dirt or dust that may have collected on the blinds. You'll then want to seal the blinds in place with silicone caulk. 
You can learn more about cleaning window blinds by reading our how-to page. 


[!] To adjust the height of your window blinds, you'll first need to measure the distance between the inside of your window and the bottom of the window blinds. You'll want to adjust the height of the blinds so that the blinds are close to the bottom of your window. instruction:
Give a brief explanation of the requested part of the paper.

Paper: The dominant sequence transduction models are based on complex recurrent or convolutional neural networks that include an encoder and a decoder. The best performing models also connect the encoder and decoder through an attention mechanism. We propose a new simple network architecture, the Transformer, based solely on attention mechanisms, dispensing with recurrence and convolutions entirely. Experiments on two machine translation tasks show these models to be superior in quality while being more parallelizable and requiring significantly less time to train. Our model achieves 28.4 BLEU on the WMT 2014 English-to-German translation task, improving over the existing best results, including ensembles, by over 2 BLEU. On the WMT 2014 English-to-French translation task, our model establishes a new single-model state-of-the-art BLEU score of 41.8 after training for 3.5 days on eight GPUs, a small fraction of the training costs of the best models from the literature. We show that the Transformer generalizes well to other tasks by applying it successfully to English constituency parsing both with large and limited training data.

output:
Model: Transformer

https://arxiv.org/abs/1810.04805

Description: Transformer is a new sequence transduction model based on an encoder-decoder architecture. The model consists of a sequence encoder and a sequence decoder. The encoder maps words into vectors and the decoder generates outputs from the encoder’s hidden states. The encoder consists of two sublayers: a bidirectional long short-term memory (LSTM) unit followed by a feedforward GRU unit. The model achieves state-of-the-art results in several natural language processing (NLP) tasks such as machine translation, speech recognition, and semantic parsing. The Transformer model can be used as a sequence transduction model in a variety of NLP tasks. For example, it can be used to translate sentences in a parallel corpus, or it can be used to generate summaries of the input sentences. The Transformer model is also suitable for sequence-to-sequence models, such as recurrent neural networks (RNNs). The Transformer model is well suited for tasks such as machine translation and speech recognition, and is commonly used in these tasks. The model is also used in a variety of other tasks such as semantic parsing, constituency parsing, and summarization.

Trained on the BLEU dataset, the Transformer achieved the highest BLEU score on the English-to-German translation task with a new state-of-the-art BLEU score of 42.8, improving over the previous best results by over 2 BLEU. The Transformer model also achieved a new BLEU score of 41.8 on the English-to-French translation task, which is the second best result in the literature. The Transformer model is trained on eight GPUs, and on average takes around 1.5 hours to train on the English-to-German translation task.

The Transformer model is a simple and effective sequence transduction model, with few parameters and no parameters in the recurrent or convolutional sublayers. The model is highly parallelizable, requiring significantly less training time than existing models. The Transformer model can be trained on a single GPU, which significantly reduces the training time and improves the model’s performance. The Transformer model is highly effective in natural language processing tasks, such as machine translation, and is commonly used in these tasks. For example, it has been used in machine translation and speech recognition, and it is also being studied in the field of semantic parsing.

instruction: When was Canada colonized?
output: Colonization of Canada began in the mid-19th century with the British Empire expanding its reach throughout the continent. Britain's goal was to establish a colony of British North America, a concept that would later evolve into the Dominion of Canada. Britain's initial goal was to establish a colony in the Pacific Ocean, with plans to use the colony to trade with China. Canada would later be established as a British colony, with the current constitution being adopted in 1867. Canada would eventually expand to become the fifth-largest country in the world.

output:
Scenario:

You want to know the total cost of constructing a 3x4 table.


Steps:

1.  Calculate the total cost of constructing a 3x4 table.

2.  Subtract the total cost of the two side tables.

3.  Add the cost of the two end tables.

4.  Add the cost of the two end caps.

5.  Total the total cost.

6.  Multiply the total cost by the number of sides.

7.  Add the total to the original cost to get the total cost of the 3x4 table.

instruction: I want to learn more about airplanes. How were they created?
output: The development of airplanes began in the early 19th century when the Wright brothers designed a two-seater plane that was powered by a single propeller. The Wright brothers then improved their design, and in 1903 the first successful aircraft, the Wright Flyer, was flown. The first successful commercial flight took place in 1905, and in 1914, the first jet airplane, the Boeing Stratocruiser, was built. Jet planes replaced the Wright Flyer and Stratocruiser, and continue to be very important to the aviation industry.

output:
poem about a family sailing vacation in Bora Bora in the style of Robert Frost

Dear Family,

This summer I've been taking the kids on a family sail vacation in Bora Bora. It's a beautiful island with miles of coral reefs and crystal-clear waters. The kids are so happy to be out on the water and the sun is shining. We've been sailing along the coast of Bora Bora, visiting the beach and the crystal-clear waters of the sea. It's a beautiful day, and I'm so glad we're out on the water. We're enjoying the warm sun and the beautiful scenery, and the kids are having a great time. I hope you're enjoying your vacation, too.

Love,

Robert Frost

instruction: How do polar bears stay warm in Arctic winters?
output: Bears have a wide range of adaptations that help them survive in cold temperatures, such as thick fur that keeps their bodies warm, and thick hair on their legs that helps them move through the snow. They also have a thick layer of blubber under their fur that helps them stay warm. Finally, they have thick toes that help them grip the snow for stability.

instruction:
Describe how to prepare the given food in your own words. Note down the ingredients you will need and the steps you will take to prepare them.

Chewy Chocolate Chip Cookies
output:
Warm the butter, then add the brown sugar, baking powder, and salt and stir until the mixture is well mixed.

Gradually add the chocolate chips, stirring until they are evenly incorporated.


Stir in the milk and vanilla and mix until the dough is smooth and no longer clumpy.


Turn the dough out onto a lightly floured surface and knead until the dough is smooth and no longer sticky.

Wrap the dough in plastic wrap and chill for 30 minutes.

Roll the dough out on a lightly floured surface to a thickness of 1/4 inch and cut into 2-inch rounds.

Place the cookies on an ungreased cookie sheet and bake for 10 minutes, or until the cookies are golden brown.

Let the cookies cool completely on the cookie sheet.

When cool, transfer the cookies to a wire rack to cool completely.

Store the cookies in an airtight container at room temperature for up to 2 days.

Enjoy!

Yield: About 2 dozen cookies

instruction: I like to host guests at my home from time to time, and I am gathering  recipes of different dishes and drinks to keep things interesting. I am interested in trying some Israeli dishes. Can you give me a recipe Israeli Cheese Bourekas?
output:
Israeli Cheese Bourekas

This appetizer is made with potatoes, a cheesy sauce, and a variety of vegetables. It's a great dish to serve with a salad. You can find the recipe here:

"Israeli Cheese Bourekas"

Ingredients

2 pounds potatoes

1/2 cup freshly grated Parmesan cheese

1/4 cup grated Romano cheese

1/2 cup grated Asiago cheese

1 tablespoon chopped fresh parsley

1/4 cup chopped fresh chives

1/2 teaspoon dried oregano

1/4 teaspoon salt

1/2 teaspoon freshly ground pepper

1/4 cup olive oil

1 tablespoon butter

1. Pierce potatoes with fork and microwave until soft, about 10 minutes.

2. Combine potatoes, Parmesan cheese, Romano cheese, Asiago cheese, parsley, chives, oregano, salt, and pepper in bowl.

3. Heat oil and butter in large skillet over medium heat. Add potato mixture and cook, stirring, until heated through, about 5 minutes.

instruction: What is the best way to form a new habit?

Dear visitor,

Habits are things that we do repeatedly to improve our quality of life. They can be conscious or unconscious, and they can be small or large. Habits can help us be more organized, focused, and effective.

A good habit is one that we can do without thinking about it. It's also one that we can carry out without much effort or conscious thought.

A good habit, then, is one that you can form easily and automatically, without much thought or conscious effort.

Some habits that are good to form include:

- Washing your hands often
- Maintaining a regular sleep schedule
- Maintaining a healthy diet
- Planning ahead for the future

Some good habits to form include:

- Having a regular morning routine
- Washing hands before eating or before doing any other activities
- Keeping track of what we eat and drink
- Maintaining a healthy weight
- Planning ahead for the future
- Maintaining a regular exercise schedule

You can also develop other habits, such as learning to manage stress or learning to set goals for the future.

You can learn more about habits and developing good ones by reading Habits for Life: A Promising Path to a More Effective Life, by Dr. Timothy Wilson, and by watching some of his popular videos on YouTube.

You can also search online for related topics, such as "how to form a new habit" or "how to develop good habits."

My recipe for Danish creamed potatoes is:

-Make a creamed potato by combining 1 cup of milk, 1 cup of potato, and 1/2 teaspoon of salt.
-Heat a heavy skillet over medium heat. Add 2 tablespoons of butter and swirl to coat the pan.
-Add 1 cup of potatoes and cook until they begin to soften, about 5 minutes.
-Add 1/2 cup of sour cream and cook until the potatoes are creamy.
-Mix in 1/2 cup of sour cream, 1/2 cup of cream cheese, and 1 tablespoon of butter.
-Add 1/2 teaspoon of salt and pepper to taste.
-Cover and cook until the potatoes are heated through, about 5 minutes.
-Serve warm.

Provide a Java solution to the following problem.

Given an integer n, return true if it is a power of three. Otherwise, return false.
An integer n is a power of three, if there exists an integer x such that n == 3^x.

Example 1:
In: n = 27
Out: true
Explanation: 27 = 3^3

Example 2:
In: n = 0
Out: false
Explanation: There is no x where 3^x = 0.

Example 3:
In: n = -1
Out: false
Explanation: There is no x where 3x = (-1).
 
Constraints:
-231 <= n <= 231 - 1
Follow up: Could you solve it without loops/recursion?

Scenario: A company is developing a new product or service. They are considering starting a waitlist for the new product. What should they do?


A waitlist is a way for a company to get a feel for how many customers would be interested in a new product or service before it is ready to launch. Waitlists can help a company decide whether it is ready to launch a new product or service, and they can also help the company decide whether it should offer a new product or service in the future.

instruction: Can you help me write a formal email to a potential business partner proposing a joint venture?
output:
Dear prospective business partner,

The best way to find the right person to partner with is to find out as much as you can about the other person. Do they have a business background or experience in the industry? Do they have a good reputation? Do they have any special skills or knowledge you can benefit from? Do they have any hobbies or interests you can discuss? Do they have any questions you want answered? Do they have any questions you want answered? Do they seem to be a good person to work with?

Before you agree to partner with someone, make sure you know as much as you can about them. The more information you have, the better able you will be to make a good decision about whether they're a good match for you. 

If you have any questions about the partnership, please don't hesitate to contact me. I'll be happy to help.

It consists of the study, diagnosis, prevention, management, and treatment of diseases, disorders, and conditions of the mouth, most commonly focused on dentition (the development and arrangement of teeth) as well as the oral mucosa. Dentistry may also encompass other aspects of the craniofacial complex including the temporomandibular joint. The practitioner is called a dentist.

Robert Alpert was born in Chicago, Illinois. He graduated from the University of Illinois College of Dentistry in 1974 and completed his residency at the University of Illinois College of Dentistry in 1975. He went on to complete a fellowship in oral surgery at the University of Pennsylvania School of Dental Medicine in Philadelphia, Pennsylvania. He is the author of several books on dentistry and oral medicine, including How to Be a Dentist, Dental Anatomy, and Dentistry: A Physician's Guide. He has also written articles for several dental journals and magazines.

Alpert's clinical practice focuses on preventive dentistry, including oral hygiene, oral care instruction, and treatment of dental problems. He also performs a variety of surgical and restorative dental procedures, including root canal therapy, implant placement, tooth extraction, and endodontic therapy. He has been involved in a variety of clinical studies of oral health and disease, and is an active member of the American Dental Association. instruction: What happened to schrodinger's cat?
output:
U

Schrodinger's cat was a thought experiment by the German physicist Erwin Schrödinger. In his 1927 book What Is Life?, Schrödinger proposed that a cat in a box could be in either of two states -- an "e" or "i" state. If the cat was in an "e" state, it would be alive, but if it was in an "i" state, it would be dead. Schrödinger proposed that the cat would be in an "e" state if it was alive, but in an "i" state if it was dead.

instruction: How do I cook a salmon fillet on a stove top pan?
output: Scrub the salmon, and pat the fish dry with paper towels. Place the salmon on a plate and patting the fish dry, layer the fish with the tomato sauce. Cover with the bread crumbs and bake for 15 to 20 minutes, until the fish is flaky and the sauce is bubbling. Let the fillets rest for 2 to 3 minutes before serving.

ascending order

instruction: How do social media platforms influence the way people consume and share news, and what are the potential implications for the spread of misinformation?
output: Social media platforms have become essential tools for connecting people around the world and facilitating communication and collaboration. Social media platforms allow for the free and rapid flow of information, which can be used to spark civic engagement and to organize protests and political discourse. instruction: What are some species of bears that are now extinct?
output: Bears are mammals that are large, carnivorous, and generally nocturnal. They can be found throughout much of North and South America, and are also found in Eurasia and Africa. Bears are included on the IUCN Red List of Threatened Animals, and are also the subject of substantial conservation efforts. Bears are threatened by human development, such as logging, agriculture, and urban development, as well as by a variety of other threats, such as climate change and degradation of ecosystems. Bears are also vulnerable to disease, and a variety of threats, including collisions with vehicles and power lines, and the illegal hunting and exploitation of bears for their meat and fur. Bears are also subject to severe conservation efforts, including captive breeding and reintroduction programs, as well as restrictions on hunting and trade in certain regions, and efforts by governments and conservation groups to reduce the threats facing bears. Bears are classified as endangered throughout much of their range, and are threatened throughout most of their range by human development, as well as by a variety of other threats, including disease, habitat loss, and degradation of ecosystems.

Implementing a Remote Working Policy
output:
= Information about the Remote Work Policy.= In a remote working policy, you have a set of responsibilities that apply to you when you work remotely. It’s important to understand your responsibilities and the reasons you’re working remotely. The following are some of the most important responsibilities you should have when working remotely.

-You should set clear expectations for your remote work relationships. You should define the roles and responsibilities of each person on your team and communicate those expectations clearly. -You should communicate regularly and openly with your team about your work remotely and about your expectations for the relationship. -You should be able to respond to emergencies in a timely and effective way. -You should set clear limits on your time spent working remotely and communicate those limits clearly. = Pros and Cons of Working Remotely.= There are several advantages to working remotely. The most important advantages are flexibility and increased collaboration. You can work from anywhere in the world, and you can work from anywhere at any time. You can work on projects with different groups of people, and you can work with different time zones. You can work on projects that have different deadlines and different requirements.

-Remote work can be a great way to increase collaboration and increase your effectiveness at work. You can work on projects that are bigger and more complex than usual, and you can have more access to information and insights that you might not have otherwise. -Working remotely can allow you to work with different types of people and different types of teams, which can help you to become a better team leader. -Working remotely can give you the opportunity to work on projects with different deadlines and different requirements. This can help you to be more efficient and effective.

= Tips for Implementing a Remote Working Policy.= To help you get started, here are some tips for implementing a remote working policy.

-Set clear expectations for your remote work relationships. -Communicate regularly and openly with your team about your work remotely and your expectations for the relationship. -Set clear limits on your time spent working remotely and communicate those limits clearly. -Set clear limits on your time spent working remotely and communicate those limits clearly. = Questions to Ask Before Working Remotely.

-What is the purpose of my remote work policy? -What are the expectations for the relationship? -What are the responsibilities and expectations of each person on my team? -What are the limitations on my time spent working remotely? -What are the expectations for communication? -What are the expectations for emergencies? = Resources for Implementing a Remote Working Policy.= For more information about implementing a remote working policy, check with your company’s human resources department or HR department. instruction: What if the Maya civilization had never mysteriously collapsed?
output: Story: The Maya civilization, which flourished in the Maya Lowlands of Central America from about A.D. 200 to 900, was one of the most prosperous and technologically advanced civilizations in the ancient world. It was known for its advanced writing, advanced mathematics, advanced astronomical calendars, advanced calendar systems, advanced art, and advanced architecture. It is estimated that the Maya civilization produced more writing and mathematics than any other civilization of the time, and the Maya are credited with inventing a number of key elements of early civilization, including the calendar, the zodiac, the cosmos, and the calendar month. The Maya are also known for their advanced architecture, advanced sculpture, and advanced astronomy. Many Maya sites have been discovered around the world, and many of the sites have been explored and studied in recent years. However, the Maya civilization came to an abrupt end around A.D. 800, due to a series of major earthquakes and volcanic eruptions. The Maya civilization is estimated to have been at its height around 900 A.D., and it appears to have been one of the most technologically advanced civilizations of the time. However, the Maya civilization collapsed suddenly and mysteriously around A.D. 800, and was never replaced by a successor civilization.

instruction: How can I develop my critical thinking skills?
output:
Dear Assistant,

The best way to develop your critical thinking skills is to take classes that practice thinking critically and to use these skills when you have a choice to make in a complex situation. For example, you might be asked to evaluate the pros and cons of several possible courses of action in a business situation, or you might be asked to evaluate the relative importance of several potential options in making a difficult decision. You also will need to use critical thinking skills when you have to evaluate a new product or a scientific hypothesis, or when you have to come to a conclusion about an important issue that you are facing in your daily life.

You can develop critical thinking skills by reading books that focus on thinking critically, taking classes in these topics, and by practicing the skills in small-group discussions and assignments. You can also enhance your critical thinking skills by working on a challenging project, such as a research paper or an essay.


Also, you can build up your critical thinking skills by organizing your thoughts carefully and by focusing on clarifying your reasons for making decisions and reaching conclusions. instruction: Can you explain the basics of quantum computing?

Quantum computing is a relatively new science that uses the laws of quantum mechanics to perform complex calculations quickly and efficiently. instruction: How can L’Hopital’s Rule be used in day to day life?
output: L'Hopital's Rule is a medical principle that states that if a symptom persists or worsens despite treatment, it is likely that the cause of the condition is related to the disease. This means that the condition should be investigated further, and appropriate treatment should be sought if necessary. It is one of the principles of medicine for deciding when to treat a patient with a disease.

Then, set the mixture aside. In a large bowl, beat together 1 cup of heavy cream, 1 cup of sugar, and 1 egg until smooth. Stir in the flour mixture until well blended. Pour the mixture into a greased 9-inch square baking pan. Bake the cobbler at 350 degrees for 50 minutes. Remove the cobbler from the oven and let it cool in the pan for 10 minutes. In a small bowl, mix together 1/2 cup of butter and 1 cup of powdered sugar. Drizzle the mixture over the top of the cobbler. Cut the cobbler into squares and serve it warm with whipped cream.

Hi! You're listening to Morning Edition, the daily radio news interview. I'm Steve Inskeep. Today, we're talking about the government jobs that are becoming increasingly scarce in the United States.

The federal government employs about 150,000 people, and about half of them work in the public sector. Most of them are part of the social services, like the unemployment office or the food stamp office, and they do an important job in helping people who are out of work find work.

But the jobs that are becoming less and less common are those in the private sector, like the jobs in the Treasury Department, or the jobs in the White House. Those jobs are more difficult to find, because they require a lot of background training and experience. And also they pay less. So those are the kinds of jobs that are in great demand, but they're also in great demand because of the political climate in the United States.

The jobs that are becoming more and more scarce are jobs in the government, like the jobs in the military or the jobs in the national parks. Those jobs are more difficult to find and pay more than the private sector jobs. And also they're more political. The government is expected to do a lot more of the social services, like paying for things like Social Security and unemployment insurance, and it's much more political.

And also, the government is expected to do a lot more. So it's becoming more difficult for people to find a job in the government. And that's a very sad story for many people who are in the government and who want to work in the government.

instruction:
Create a short, concise summary of the paper based on its abstract.

Few-shot learning (FSL) is one of the key future steps in machine learning and raises a lot of attention. In this paper, we focus on the FSL problem of dialogue understanding, which contains two closely related tasks: intent detection and slot filling. Dialogue understanding has been proven to benefit a lot from jointly learning the two sub-tasks. However, such joint learning becomes challenging in the few-shot scenarios: on the one hand, the sparsity of samples greatly magnifies the difficulty of modeling the connection between the two tasks; on the other hand, how to jointly learn multiple tasks in the few-shot setting is still less investigated. In response to this, we introduce FewJoint, the first FSL benchmark for joint dialogue understanding. FewJoint provides a new corpus with 59 different dialogue domains from real industrial API and a code platform to ease FSL experiment set-up, which are expected to advance the research of this field. Further, we find that insufficient performance of the few-shot setting often leads to noisy sharing between two sub-task and disturbs joint learning. To tackle this, we guide slot with explicit intent information and propose a novel trust gating mechanism that blocks low-confidence intent information to ensure high quality sharing. Besides, we introduce a Reptile-based meta-learning strategy to achieve better generalization in unseen few-shot domains. In the experiments, the proposed method brings significant improvements on two datasets and achieve new state-of-the-art performance.

instruction:
Create a daily itinerary based on the given information.

Our family is looking for a 9-day Morocco trip that has light to moderate activity levels.
output:
Travel:

- Plan activities in advance, especially when visiting cities or popular destinations.
- Choose a hotel that fits your needs and budget.
- Research local events and attractions, and book excursions to prepare for your trip.
- Also consider cultural and sightseeing tours.
- Include plenty of time for relaxation.
- Bring a multilingual travel guide and local maps for the cities you will be visiting.
- Bring a camera for snapping photos and recording videos of the sights you see.
- Before your trip, consult travel insurance to cover routine medical needs and disaster relief.
- Keep medical and travel documents together for your safety and protection.
- Consider packing a medical kit with medicines, medical supplies, and a first-aid kit.
- Also bring a sun protection device and sunglasses.
- Remember to fill your travel insurance and refund or pay for any unforeseen medical costs while you are traveling.
- Before your trip, discuss your travel plans with your doctor and pharmacist to make sure you are well informed about any medications you may need while traveling.
- Pack a list of emergency contact numbers, including your doctor and pharmacist, in case of an emergency.
- Pack a list of emergency contacts for your travel insurance, so you and your family can contact you if you have any health problems or medical concerns while traveling.

instruction: I like to host guests at my home from time to time, and I am gathering  recipes of different dishes and drinks to keep things interesting. I am interested in trying some Argentinian dishes. Can you give me a recipe for Milanesa de peceto?
output: Cooking can be a very rewarding hobby, and it can also be very creative. Chef-owner Ann Trason from Argentinian restaurant Tras-Uno has created many delicious recipes using Argentinian ingredients. Her Milanesa de Peceto is a hearty, flavorful stew made with potatoes and beans, and it is traditionally served with homemade tortillas and a spicy salsa. You can make the dish ahead and reheat it gently the next day. It is delicious served with a simple salad or warm bread. You'll enjoy the rich flavor of the stew as well as the fresh, light flavors of the vegetables and beans.

Suetonius was a historian who wrote about the history of Rome during the first century A.D. He wrote the book in order to chronicle the history of Rome from the founding of the city to the end of the Roman Empire in A.D. 4. In the book, Suetonius chronicled the history of Rome from its founding until the end of the Roman Empire in A.D. 476. instruction: How would the Future of AI in 10 Years look?
output:
Future of AI

Artificial intelligence (AI) is the science of developing machines that have the ability to mimic human intelligence. AI has the potential to outperform humans in a variety of contexts, such as performing tasks that require reasoning, learning from experience, and planning. AI can help people in many situations, including search, recommendation systems, and virtual assistants. Artificial intelligence could also help companies improve their services by analyzing data to make better decisions. AI may also become an important component of medical diagnosis and treatment.

The first generation of AI systems were designed with very simple tasks in mind. Today, there are many different kinds of AI systems, including chatbots, machine learning systems, and deep learning systems. A key challenge in developing AI systems is making them useful and efficient. AI systems need to be flexible and adaptive, and they also need to be able to learn from experience. AI systems are still in their early stages of development, and many issues need to be addressed before they can be considered a real solution to many human problems.

instruction: Suggest a recipe for a vegan dessert.
output:
Build a Bundt Cake

Stir together:

2 cups brown sugar

1/2 cup white sugar

1/2 cup vegetable oil

1/2 cup cornstarch

1/2 cup water

2 eggs

2 teaspoons baking powder

1 teaspoon vanilla extract

1/2 teaspoon salt

1 cup flour

1/2 teaspoon baking soda

1/2 teaspoon salt

1/2 cup semisweet chocolate chips

1/2 cup chopped pecans

Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F.

In a large bowl, combine the brown sugar, white sugar, oil, cornstarch, water, eggs, baking powder, vanilla extract, and salt.

In another bowl, combine the flour, baking soda, salt, and chocolate chips.

Add the flour mixture to the sugar mixture and stir to combine.

Pour the batter into a greased Bundt pan.

Bake for 30 to 35 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.

Let the Bundt cake cool for 10 minutes before inverting it onto a serving plate.

Sprinkle with the pecans and serve warm.

instruction: I like to host guests at my home from time to time, and I am gathering  recipes of different dishes and drinks to keep things interesting. I am interested in trying some Danish dishes. Can you give me a recipe for Koldskål?
output:
Recipe: Koldskål Koldskål is a traditional Danish dish of boiled cabbage with a mayonnaise sauce. The recipe uses a number of ingredients and takes about 45 minutes to prepare. This recipe is from the 1960s, and is still popular today. It can be served as a light meal or a main dish. It is usually served with boiled potatoes or rice. Ingredients 1 tablespoon vegetable oil 1 large onion, finely chopped 1 teaspoon paprika 1 cup ketchup 1 cup mayonnaise 1 cup sour cream 2 tablespoons minced fresh dill 2 teaspoons minced fresh chives 1 teaspoon Worcestershire sauce 1 teaspoon salt 1 teaspoon freshly ground black pepper 1 cup shredded cabbage Preparation 1. Heat the oil in a large saucepan over medium heat. Add the onion and paprika and saute for 5 minutes. 2. Add the ketchup, mayonnaise, sour cream, dill, chives, Worcestershire sauce, salt, and pepper. Cook over medium heat for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally. 3. Add the cabbage and cook until it is tender, about 5 minutes. 4. Serve the koldskål hot, with boiled potatoes or rice. <<

A study published earlier this year by Zee and her team examined the role of light in sleep for healthy adults in their 20s. Sleeping for only one night with a dim light, such as a TV set with the sound off, raised the blood sugar and heart rate of the young people during the sleep lab experiment. Sciences

The James Webb Space Telescope will be a space telescope designed to study the universe in infrared wavelengths. It will conduct research into the origins of the universe and the formation of galaxies. Scientists hope to learn more about how the universe began and what it will be like in the future, including how it will change with the discovery of new phenomena like dark energy. Cookies are small text files that are stored on your computer when you visit a website. They are usually placed on your computer to help you personalize your experience on the website. Cookies can help websites remember things you have visited, such as your preferences or the topics you have searched for. instruction: Please tell me the history of Walt Disney.
output:
History

Disney was created in 1928 by Walt Disney, who came from a family of animators. Walt Disney wanted to create a movie studio that would produce animation that would be a big part of the American entertainment industry. Disney was inspired to create the studio after seeing a newsreel of a Disney film called Dumbo. Disney quickly became a huge success, and he began to create many other animated features.

Disney's early films included Snow White and the Seven Dwarfs, Dumbo, Peter Pan, Alice in Wonderland, and other favorites. In the 1950s, Disney produced many more animated features, such as Bambi, Fantasia, and The Jungle Book. In the 1960s and 1970s, Disney continued to produce many more animated features, such as 101 Dalmatians, The Little Mermaid, Beauty and the Beast, and The Lion King.

Disney's many animated features have influenced and influenced modern animation. His work has influenced many artists and filmmakers, including George Lucas, Hayao Miyazaki, and John Lasseter. Disney's studio is now called Pixar Animation Studios.

Disney's most famous film is The Little Mermaid, which he co-produced with Ariel and director Alfonso Cuarón. The Little Mermaid tells the story of a young mermaid who is taken to live in the sea, and learns to become a woman. It is a well-known Disney film that has received many awards and acclaim.

instruction: What breed dog is smallest?
output:
Basset hound

The Basset hound is one of the smallest breeds, standing about 12 to 14 inches tall, and weighing about 12 to 15 pounds. It has a short, round face, short legs, and a short, blunt muzzle. The Basset hound has a long, narrow head, and is well-balanced. It has a soft, thick coat of short, dense fur. It has a long, sturdy neck, and a flat, rounded back. It has a long, sturdy tail, and a flexible gait. It is an active, playful breed. It is an excellent guard dog, and is well-suited to a range of homes.

Pygame is a powerful, free, open-source cross-platform gaming framework for creating 2D games. Pygame provides the basic building blocks for developing games in a clean and efficient manner, including: an event system for handling input, a screen-coordinating module for drawing on the screen, a physics engine for rendering objects on the screen, a sound engine for playing sounds, and a game loop for executing game logic. Pygame is written in C and is free and open-source software. You can download Pygame for free from its website [1].

instruction: Write a compelling product launch announcement email to inform our customers of our new software solution.
output:
Build a great product launch announcement

The product launch announcement is an important step in the product life cycle. It helps ensure that your product is well received by your target audience and also establishes your credibility as a leader in the space. It’s also an opportunity to explain your unique value proposition and to showcase the features of your new product. 


Here are a few things to keep in mind when writing a product launch announcement:

- Include a compelling message that highlights the benefits of your new product and what sets it apart from its competitors.
- Be sure to include screenshots or other visuals that show off the new features and functionality of your product.
- Be sure to include a call to action for signups or download links.
- Be sure to include a short video that shows how your product works and highlights its key features.
- Use a conversational tone when writing your announcement. Your target audience is looking for a more personal connection than a standard sales pitch.
- Be sure to include a link to a demo or sample to show off your new product.
- Be sure to include a clear call to action for signups or download links.
- Be sure to include a short video that shows how your product works and highlights its key features.

instruction: How is oil turned into gasoline?
output: Oil is turned into gasoline by adding water to it and then heating or burning it to make it burn. The oil is first mixed with water to form a liquid called a crude oil. The crude oil is then heated to crack it down into a lighter liquid called kerosene. The cracked oil is then heated or burned to turn it into gasoline.

instruction: Hi, I'd like to make my own peanut brittle. Can you give me a recipe and cooking instructions for that?
output:
Cooking Instructions

To make peanut brittle, in a large saucepan combine 1 cup sugar, 1/2 cup peanut butter, and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla extract. Cook over medium heat until the sugar and peanut butter are melted and the mixture is smooth. Remove from the heat and stir in 1/4 cup peanuts. Let cool completely, then refrigerate until firm.

To serve, cut the peanut brittle into squares or triangles. Store the brittle in an airtight container at room temperature for up to 2 weeks.

output: The best way to reduce your alcohol consumption is to recognize that alcohol is addictive, and to learn how to stop drinking it. Many people start drinking alcohol to cope with stressful situations or to have a pleasant, social experience. However, drinking alcohol can be harmful, and people who continue to drink large amounts of it become dependent on it. Some evidence shows that heavy drinking is also linked to many health problems, such as liver disease, heart disease, and some forms of cancer. Many people who drink alcohol start by trying to cut down or avoid it completely, but this may not work. Recovery from addiction to alcohol or other drugs is a long, difficult process that requires treatment from a medical professional. Alcohol dependence can be treated with therapy and support from a community-based program. Research shows that treatment from a mental health provider can help people recovering from alcohol addiction to stop drinking altogether or to reduce their drinking.

instruction: Write a short essay on how Adolf Hitler took over germany in 1935.
output:
Build a Plot

Hitler's rise to power is the stuff of legend. He rose to power through a series of carefully orchestrated political maneuvers, and his rise to power is widely considered one of the most significant events in 20th-century history. In this essay, you'll learn more about Hitler's rise to power and how it affected the course of world history.


Hitler's rise to power

Hitler came to power in Germany in 1933, when the country was still in the midst of the Great Depression. Hitler initially attempted to increase the role of the state in the economy, but he was soon overwhelmed by political opposition and opposition from within the Nazi party. He was eventually forced to resign in 1938, and he died in 1945.


Hitler's rise to power was a slow process, and it was not until the end of World War II that the Nazi party began to gain significant support. - clarifying expectations and goals

This process is thought to play a role in the evolution of many traits in animals and plants, including colors, sounds, and patterns.

instruction: how much of a threat is climate change in the coming years, and what should we do to stop it?
output:
Scenario

Climate change represents a threat to human health and well-being, because it is caused by a change in the natural environment, and humans have an impact on the environment. The best way to reduce the threat of climate change is to reduce human activities that cause emissions of climate-changing greenhouse gases. People can help to reduce human activities that cause emissions of climate-changing greenhouse gases, including reducing energy use and improving energy efficiency in buildings. People can also reduce their own activities that contribute to climate change, including reducing their own energy use and improving energy efficiency in homes, businesses, and public transportation. People can also adopt energy-conserving behaviors, including reducing their personal consumption of energy and using energy wisely. People can also reduce their travel, particularly by using public transportation and car sharing. People can also reduce their greenhouse gas emissions at home, work, and play.

Tips for reducing climate change

People can make changes in their lives that help reduce emissions of greenhouse gases, such as switching to energy-efficient light bulbs and using public transportation. People can also reduce energy use in their homes, businesses, and public transportation. They can also reduce their own consumption of energy, and adopt energy-conserving behaviors, including using energy wisely.

For more information about reducing climate change, people can visit the Environmental Protection Agency's website.

instruction: How do I check my system drive for errors on Windows?
output:
A system drive is a special type of storage medium used in computers to store data and programs. It is most commonly a hard disk drive or solid-state drive, but it also can be a CD-ROM drive, a tape drive, a flash drive, a memory card, a digital video disk (DVD), or a compact flash card.


To check your system drive, open a Windows Explorer window. From the File menu, choose "Properties." In the "Computer" tab, click the "System" tab. Click the "Storage" button. You can also view the properties of individual files on the drive, or you can click the "Details" button to view the details of a file.


You can also perform a hard drive test to determine if any files are in error or have been corrupted. To perform a hard drive test, open a command prompt and navigate to the path where you saved all of your files. Enter "fsutil scanhard" and follow the on-screen instructions. The command will perform a basic hard drive scan and will show you any errors it finds.

output:

Kammounia is a Tunisian dish made from chickpeas, which is a tasty and healthy side dish. It can be prepared with various vegetables and can also be served with rice or bulgar wheat. The dish is made by frying chickpeas and then adding spices and lemon juice to it. It is often served with rice.

Sincerely,

The Assistant

The Spanish also forced the indigenous people to work long hours for low wages, and then sold them into slavery in the Americas.


After the Spanish arrived in the Americas, the native people began to rebel against their Spanish colonial rulers. instruction: I like to host guests at my home from time to time, and I am gathering  recipes of different dishes and drinks to keep things interesting. I am interested in trying some Georgian  dishes. Can you give me a recipe for Kubdari?
output:
recipe: Kubdari

Kubdari is a Georgian stew made with lamb and vegetables. The stew is usually served with rice or bread, and is usually made with potatoes, onions, and spices. It is also often served with yogurt and olives. Kubdari can be served with rice or bread, and is usually very hearty.




This recipe is from the "Georgian Cookery" book by Elisavet Belokobolsky. Other recipes from the book include Kvareltsi, a stew with meat, potatoes, onions, and carrots; Kvarketi, a stew with lamb, potatoes, and peas; and Kvarketi Gogare, a stew with lamb, potatoes, carrots, and peas.

instruction:
A statistical model is a mathematical model that embodies a set of statistical assumptions concerning the generation of sample data (and similar data from a larger population). A statistical model represents, often in considerably idealized form, the data-generating process.

A statistical model is usually specified as a mathematical relationship between one or more random variables and other non-random variables. As such, a statistical model is "a formal representation of a theory" (Herman Adèr quoting Kenneth Bollen).

All statistical hypothesis tests and all statistical estimators are derived via statistical models. More generally, statistical models are part of the foundation of statistical inference.

Could you explain each sentence in simple terms?
output:
Statistical models are used to make statistical predictions about observed data, such as how many people will visit a location, how long they will stay, or how much money they will make. The models are used to describe what is happening in the real world and make predictions about future outcomes. They also help researchers in science, engineering, and other areas.

The models used in statistics are usually complex, but they are not always correct. Many statistical models are based on observations of data, and they are not meant to describe reality. Researchers should carefully check the assumptions in a statistical model to ensure that they accurately represent the data they are trying to analyze.

instruction: I want to get better at networking at work
output:
Dear user,

The best way to get better at networking is to practice, both at home and at work. You can practice by doing activities that require networking, or by talking with colleagues about how you can improve your skills. You can also try new hobbies, such as taking classes in IT, or becoming involved in a local networking group. You can also visit local job fairs and talk with employers about your skills and interests.

Tips for practicing at work include:

 * Meet new people. Networking with colleagues and managers helps you build your professional network.
 * Know your strengths and interests. By learning about your skills and interests, you will be able to set goals for your career and find new opportunities.
 * Communicate effectively. By building strong professional relationships, you will be able to speak up for your opinions and ideas, and show that you are an effective team player.
 * Become involved in local organizations. Networking with local organizations like Rotary, Toastmasters, and Kiwanis will help you build your career network and give you a local perspective on the industry.
 * Find new ways to learn. By taking classes in IT, you can increase your technical skills, and by taking networking classes, you can improve your communication and leadership skills.

If you'd like more advice about networking at work, please visit http://www.bis.gov/ncea/topics/work/networking.htm.

instruction: Implement a regular expression in Python to validate an email address.
output:
Build a regular expression that matches email addresses.

You can use the following code to generate a regular expression that matches some email addresses:

```python
import re

email = input('Please enter an email address: ')
if re.match(r'^[\w.-]+@(\w+)$', email):
    print('The email address "%s" is valid.' % email)
else:
    print('The email address "%s" is not valid.' % email)
```

instruction: How can I fix a leaking roof?
output:
The leaking roof is caused by many different factors, such as:

- heavy rain

- cold temperatures

- moisture in the soil

- fungus

- insect infestations

- birds or animal attacks

- structural problems

- improper maintenance

- broken or worn shingles

- cracks in the roof sheathing

- missing flashing

- missing flashing or rotten shingles


The symptoms of a leaking roof are:

- uneven or missing shingles

- cracks in the roof sheathing

- water that seeps through the roof

- mildew or fungus

- mold or dampness in the attic


For more information, see your local home improvement store or check with a local professional.

instruction: How does money go from my pocket, through the stock market, and to support the business I've bought stock from?
output: Money flows from your pocket through a process called "stock trading." It's like investing, but instead of buying a stock, you're buying shares of a company and selling them on the market. The company's value is determined by the value of its stock and the market price of the stock. The company's value is calculated by multiplying its shares outstanding by the price at which they're selling. Therefore, the price of a stock is actually debt for the company, since it owes the company money for each share it sells.

instruction: I've recently started playing the turn-based strategy game Into the Breach. I have read online that the game is considered to have 'perfect information'. What is meant by 'perfect information' in this context?
output: The game has perfect information if, when the game starts, there is no information about the enemy's strategy or their position that can affect the outcome of the game. In other words, the game's outcome is known exactly before it starts.

instruction:

1 avocado

1 Tbsp Dijon mustard
2 to 3 Tbsp celery, chopped
2 Tbsp red onion, chopped
2 green onions, chopped

Salt and pepper, to taste
2 heaping cups leafy green lettuce
1 cup matchstick carrots
4 (10 inch) whole wheat tortillas

instruction: I am going to try to roast a pig at home for Thanksgiving this year. What equipment and techniques do I need to successfully get a pig roasted?
output:
Dear Assistant,

Roasting a whole pig is an excellent way to prepare a meaty, tender dinner for a crowd. The general procedure is to first get the pig cleaned and prepared for cooking. Then the roast is placed on a rack in a large roasting pan and covered with olive oil. Next the roast is placed in the oven and cooked until an instant-read thermometer inserted into the thickest part of the pig registers 145 degrees.


It's important to keep the roast at a steady temperature during the entire cooking process so that it is cooked through. Also, it's important to monitor the roast from time to time to make sure that it doesn't overcook. If the roast is cooking too quickly, it can dry out and become tough.


Once the roast is cooked, it is transferred to a serving dish and the roast can be served immediately. You can also cover the roast with aluminum foil to keep it from getting too dry.

instruction: explain the basics of area and perimeter
output:
Scatterplots

The area of a region is the measure of the total surface of the region. The perimeter of a region is the measure of the longest straight line that connects all points in the region.


Scatterplots are a visual way of plotting data on a graph. The points in a scatterplot represent the values of the data. The area of the region is the sum of the points in the scatterplot. The perimeter is the longest line that connects all points.

Scatterplots are a useful tool for analyzing data and for visualizing results.

instruction: In a world where automation is becoming increasingly prevalent, is it more important to prioritize job creation or technological progress?
output:
Title:

Is it more important to prioritize job creation or technological progress?

Description:

Automation is becoming more common and has the potential to improve the lot of workers in many industries. It can be a highly productive use of resources, and it can also create new jobs. The U.S. government is encouraging companies to increase their use of automation, and many companies are adopting automated processes to cut costs and increase productivity. However, there is also increasing concern about the impact of automation on the quality of jobs. Some experts worry that increased automation could lead to increased joblessness, decreased wages, and reduced opportunities for advancement.

instruction: How can governments utilize fiscal and monetary policies to combat economic recessions?

Monetary policies can help stabilize the economy and support growth by allowing consumers and businesses to save and borrow money.

instruction:
Summarize the article you have been given in a brief manner.

Mathematics and art are related in a variety of ways. Mathematics has itself been described as an art motivated by beauty. Mathematics can be discerned in arts such as music, dance, painting, architecture, sculpture, and textiles. This article focuses, however, on mathematics in the visual arts.
Mathematics and art have a long historical relationship. Artists have used mathematics since the 4th century BC when the Greek sculptor Polykleitos wrote his Canon, prescribing proportions conjectured to have been based on the ratio 1:√2 for the ideal male nude. Persistent popular claims have been made for the use of the golden ratio in ancient art and architecture, without reliable evidence. In the Italian Renaissance, Luca Pacioli wrote the influential treatise De divina proportione (1509), illustrated with woodcuts by Leonardo da Vinci, on the use of the golden ratio in art. Another Italian painter, Piero della Francesca, developed Euclid's ideas on perspective in treatises such as De Prospectiva Pingendi, and in his paintings. The engraver Albrecht Dürer made many references to mathematics in his work Melencolia I. In modern times, the graphic artist M. C. Escher made intensive use of tessellation and hyperbolic geometry, with the help of the mathematician H. S. M. Coxeter, while the De Stijl movement led by Theo van Doesburg and Piet Mondrian explicitly embraced geometrical forms. Mathematics has inspired textile arts such as quilting, knitting, cross-stitch, crochet, embroidery, weaving, Turkish and other carpet-making, as well as kilim. In Islamic art, symmetries are evident in forms as varied as Persian girih and Moroccan zellige tilework, Mughal jali pierced stone screens, and widespread muqarnas vaulting.

instruction: What if the Black Death had not occurred in the 14th century?
output:
Scenario: The Black Death

The Black Death was a pandemic that killed millions of people between 1347 and 1351. The disease was caused by a bacterium called Yersinia pestis. Yersinia pestis is found in the soil and can survive for years. Outbreaks of the disease were most common in Northern Europe in the 14th century. The disease is spread by fleas that feed on rodents, and it is often carried in rats and mice.

The Black Death was a terrible epidemic that killed tens of millions of people worldwide. The disease is often called "the Great Plague" because it killed so many people. The disease is most common in Northern Europe, but it also affected the Mediterranean region, southern Europe, and the Middle East. The disease is estimated to have killed up to 70% of the population of Europe in the 14th century.
